# PageDAO Hub Environment Variables

This document lists all environment variables referenced in the codebase that need to be configured in Netlify deployment settings.

## Core RPC Endpoints

| Variable | Description | Default Value | Required |
|----------|-------------|---------------|----------|
| `ETH_RPC_URL` | Primary Ethereum RPC URL | https://eth.drpc.org | Yes |
| `ETH_BACKUP_RPC_URL` | Backup Ethereum RPC URL | https://eth.llamarpc.com | No |
| `OPTIMISM_RPC_URL` | Primary Optimism RPC URL | https://mainnet.optimism.io | Yes |
| `OPTIMISM_BACKUP_RPC_URL` | Backup Optimism RPC URL | https://optimism.llamarpc.com | No |
| `BASE_RPC_URL` | Primary Base RPC URL | https://mainnet.base.org | Yes |
| `BASE_BACKUP_RPC_URL` | Backup Base RPC URL | https://base.publicnode.com | No |

## Token Configuration

| Variable | Description | Default Value | Required |
|----------|-------------|---------------|----------|
| `PAGE_LOGO_URI` | URI for PAGE token logo | /images/page-token-logo.png | No |
| `CACHE_DURATION` | Duration in ms to cache token data | 300000 (5 minutes) | No |
| `DEFAULT_IMAGE_URL` | Default image URL for token | - | No |

## API Configuration

| Variable | Description | Default Value | Required |
|----------|-------------|---------------|----------|
| `REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL` or `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | API base URL for frontend | /api/v1 (prod) or http://localhost:8888/api/v1 (dev) | No |
| `REACT_APP_API_TIMEOUT` | API request timeout in ms | 30000 | No |
| `REACT_APP_API_RETRY_COUNT` | Number of retries for API requests | 2 | No |
| `REACT_APP_API_RETRY_DELAY` | Delay between retries in ms | 1000 | No |

## Dashboard Configuration

| Variable | Description | Default Value | Required |
|----------|-------------|---------------|----------|
| `REACT_APP_REFRESH_INTERVAL` | Data refresh interval in ms | 60000 | No |
| `REACT_APP_DEFAULT_THEME` | Default theme (light/dark) | dark | No |
| `REACT_APP_DEFAULT_TIMEFRAME` | Default timeframe for charts | 24h | No |

## Webhook Configuration

| Variable | Description | Default Value | Required |
|----------|-------------|---------------|----------|
| `WEBHOOK_SECRET` | Secret key for webhook authentication | - | Yes (if using webhooks) |

## Notes for Netlify Deployment

1. All variables should be set in the Netlify site's environment variables section
2. For variables with defaults, you only need to set them if you want to override the default value
3. Variables with no default value and marked as required must be set before deployment
4. The webhook secret should be a strong random value generated specifically for this purpose
5. RPC URLs should use reliable providers with sufficient rate limits for your expected traffic

## Example .env File Format

For local development, create a `.env` file in the root directory with the following format:

```
# Core RPC Endpoints
ETH_RPC_URL=https://eth.drpc.org
ETH_BACKUP_RPC_URL=https://eth.llamarpc.com
OPTIMISM_RPC_URL=https://mainnet.optimism.io
OPTIMISM_BACKUP_RPC_URL=https://optimism.llamarpc.com
BASE_RPC_URL=https://mainnet.base.org
BASE_BACKUP_RPC_URL=https://base.publicnode.com

# Token Configuration
PAGE_LOGO_URI=/images/page-token-logo.png
CACHE_DURATION=300000
DEFAULT_IMAGE_URL=https://example.com/default.png

# Webhook Configuration (if used)
WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-strong-random-secret
```

DO NOT commit this file to the repository. Add `.env` to your `.gitignore` file.